profile_positions.description:
In my role as Senior Corporate Counsel, I support Staffbase to scale by 

- advising on corporate law questions;
- supporting in M&A and post-M&A integration work;
- corporate housekeeping;

Before that I supported the DACH-market as commercial legal counsel by
- drafting/negotiating/reviewing SaaS Master Service Agreements and Order Forms;
- reviewing/drafting legal documents in German tender processes (in particular EVB-IT) and providing risk assessments;
- negotiating/reviewing purchase agreements, e.g. professional service agreements, lease agreements;
- giving advice on various legal issues related to the day to day business.

Staffbase is an enterprise SaaS platform that helps HR and Communication leaders to transform their organisations into places where people feel connected and proud to come to work. Staffbase is the first employee experience platform to let employers and employees connect authentically, right through their mobile phones.

Staffbase is a fast growing tech startup, headquartered in Chemnitz, but with offices in Dresden, Cologne, Amsterdam, London, and New York.

At Staffbase Legal, our core values are plain language, business acumen, and finding workable and pragmatic solutions to legal problems. We also practice Kaizen, or continuous improvement, and are constantly looking at how we can improve our processes, templates, and policies to improve the experience for our customers and our “Staffpranos” here at Staffbase.

In my role as Commercial Legal Counsel, EAI, I provided legal support to the Marketing & Sales organizations of LyondellBasell regarding various topics, including:

- contract drafting/review;
- contract negotiations;
- credit collection; 
- litigation/complaint handling; 
- external communications; and
- advice on various legal issues.

I supported different product groups within the Chemical and Polymers divisions of LyondellBasell. 

About LyondellBasell
LyondellBasell (NYSE: LYB) is one of the largest plastics, chemicals and refining companies in the world. Driven by its 13,400 employees around the globe, LyondellBasell produces materials and products that are key to advancing solutions to modern challenges like enhancing food safety through lightweight and flexible packaging, protecting the purity of water supplies through stronger and more versatile pipes, and improving the safety, comfort and fuel efficiency of many of the cars and trucks on the road. LyondellBasell sells products into approximately 100 countries and is the world's largest licensor of polyolefin technologies. In 2018, LyondellBasell was named to Fortune magazine's list of the "World's Most Admired Companies." More information about LyondellBasell can be found at www.LyondellBasell.com.
